HEADWORD: Acockbill
<hw>A*cock"bill`</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <ety>[Prefix
<ets>a-</ets> + <ets>cock</ets> + <ets>bill</ets>: with bills cocked
up.]</ety> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>Hanging at the cathead,
ready to let go, as an anchor.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>Topped up; having
one yardarm higher than the other.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

